# Git Rules

## Push

Do not push to GitHub unless the user explicitly instructs you to do so.
Warn the user before pushing directly to the main branch.

## Destructive operations

Never use `--force` push, `--hard` reset, or other destructive/irreversible git commands unless the user explicitly requests them.

## Commit messages

Write all commit messages in English.

## Co-authored-by

When creating a git commit, always append the following trailer to the commit message:

```
Co-authored-by: cursor <noreply@cursor.com>
```
